{
  "doc_id": "24047",
  "text": "Besides that inosine is reported to bind to adenosine receptors, other additional mechanisms were also described. Inosine may partially act by interfering with the activation of the nuclear enzyme poly(adenosine diphosphate-ribose) polymerase [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , which was involved in the regulation of inflammatory processes in acute lung injury [CITATION_3] . Inosine may also enhance endogenous antioxidant systems because inosine breakdown releases urate, a scavenger of oxyradicals and peroxynitrite [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . Thus, we can not discard that these mechanisms are involved and contributes with inosine effects observed in the current study.",
